OL,3,C'More time needed' to achieve 'best
OL,4,Cversion' of Hillsborough law
OL,6,FPressed on a timetable for bringing
OL,7,Fforward a Bill, he said: "Having
OL,8,Fconsulted with groups over recent
OL,9,Fweeks and months, we believe more time
OL,10,Fis needed to draft the best version of
OL,11,Fa Hillsborough law, but we remain
OL,12,Ffully committed to bringing this
OL,13,Flegislation at pace, and we'll
OL,14,Fobviously continue to work with them
OL,15,Fin the weeks ahead and provide an
OL,16,Fupdate when we've got it."
OL,18,FAsked if Sir Keir would apologise for
OL,19,Fthe delay, the spokesman said: "We
OL,20,Fremain fully committed to bringing
OL,21,Fthis legislation in at pace.
