OL,6,F"Our engagement with victims, families
OL,7,Fand survivors is essential to get this
OL,8,Fright, and we're committed to
OL,9,Fcontinuing to work with them on this
OL,10,Flegislation."
OL,12,FCampaigners want a legal duty of
OL,13,Fcandour on public authorities and
OL,14,Fofficials to tell the truth and
OL,15,Fproactively co-operate with official
OL,16,Finvestigations and inquiries ` with
OL,17,Fthe potential for criminal sanctions
OL,18,Ffor officials or organisations which
OL,19,Fmislead or obstruct investigations.
